cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the security and safety risks of temperature-based control systems, which involves both hardware and software components. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the potential consequences of attacks on critical systems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of analog sensors, which suggests that it could belong to cs.ET (Embedded Systems) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
